            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <p>
              Dabbling in web development over the last 25+ years has been a
              blessing and a curse. I am the quintessential _"Jack of all trades,
              master of none!"_ if I am being completely honest. I have a ton of
              experience in a lot of different areas, but never really feel like
              I have mastered a single one. Then again, that can be a good
              thing. I am very open minded and have never felt the need to follow
              any flow or trend in the industry. I have a few tools that I have
              built over the years and when I want to learn something new, I
              rebuild those tools. Compound Learning, I think that's what is
